cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with planning problems on nondeterministic domains, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new language for Linear Temporal Logic (LTL) and presents a planning algorithm based on an automata-theoretic approach, which falls under the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the complexity of the planning algorithm, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper deals with dynamic systems and execution paths, which are topics in distributed systems (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
